#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:5
msgid "Item Exporters"
msgstr "物品导出"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:10
msgid ""
"Once you have scraped your items, you often want to persist or export those "
"items, to use the data in some other application. That is, after all, the "
"whole purpose of the scraping process."
msgstr ""
"一旦你破解了你的项目，你常常想要继续或导出这些项目，以便在其他一些应用程序中"
"使用数据。 这毕竟是拆解过程的全部目的。"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:14
msgid ""
"For this purpose Scrapy provides a collection of Item Exporters for "
"different output formats, such as XML, CSV or JSON."
msgstr "为此目的，Scrapy 提供了不同输出格式的物品导出器集，如XML、CSV或JSON。"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:18
msgid "Using Item Exporters"
msgstr "使用项目导出"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you are in a hurry, and just want to use an Item Exporter to output "
"scraped data see the :ref:`topics-feed-exports`. Otherwise, if you want to "
"know how Item Exporters work or need more custom functionality (not covered "
"by the default exports), continue reading below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:25
msgid ""
"In order to use an Item Exporter, you  must instantiate it with its required "
"args. Each Item Exporter requires different arguments, so check each "
"exporter documentation to be sure, in :ref:`topics-exporters-reference`. "
"After you have instantiated your exporter, you have to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:30
msgid ""
"1. call the method :meth:`~BaseItemExporter.start_exporting` in order to "
"signal the beginning of the exporting process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:33
msgid ""
"2. call the :meth:`~BaseItemExporter.export_item` method for each item you "
"want to export"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:36
msgid ""
"3. and finally call the :meth:`~BaseItemExporter.finish_exporting` to signal "
"the end of the exporting process"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:39
msgid ""
"Here you can see an :doc:`Item Pipeline <item-pipeline>` which uses multiple "
"Item Exporters to group scraped items to different files according to the "
"value of one of their fields:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:43
msgid ""
"from itemadapter import ItemAdapter\n"
"from scrapy.exporters import XmlItemExporter\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class PerYearXmlExportPipeline:\n"
"    \"\"\"Distribute items across multiple XML files according to their "
"'year' field\"\"\"\n"
"\n"
"    def open_spider(self, spider):\n"
"        self.year_to_exporter = {}\n"
"\n"
"    def close_spider(self, spider):\n"
"        for exporter, xml_file in self.year_to_exporter.values():\n"
"            exporter.finish_exporting()\n"
"            xml_file.close()\n"
"\n"
"    def _exporter_for_item(self, item):\n"
"        adapter = ItemAdapter(item)\n"
"        year = adapter[\"year\"]\n"
"        if year not in self.year_to_exporter:\n"
"            xml_file = open(f\"{year}.xml\", \"wb\")\n"
"            exporter = XmlItemExporter(xml_file)\n"
"            exporter.start_exporting()\n"
"            self.year_to_exporter[year] = (exporter, xml_file)\n"
"        return self.year_to_exporter[year][0]\n"
"\n"
"    def process_item(self, item):\n"
"        exporter = self._exporter_for_item(item)\n"
"        exporter.export_item(item)\n"
"        return item"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:79
msgid "Serialization of item fields"
msgstr "项目字段序列化"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:81
msgid ""
"By default, the field values are passed unmodified to the underlying "
"serialization library, and the decision of how to serialize them is "
"delegated to each particular serialization library."
msgstr ""
"默认情况下，字段值将不被修改传递到底层序列化库， 每个特定的序列化图书馆都将如"
"何对其进行序列化的决定委托给每个特定的序列化图书馆。"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:85
msgid ""
"However, you can customize how each field value is serialized *before it is "
"passed to the serialization library*."
msgstr "然而，您可以自定义每个字段值在传递到序列化库之前的序列化方式*。"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:88
msgid ""
"There are two ways to customize how a field will be serialized, which are "
"described next."
msgstr "有两种方法来定制一个字段的序列化方法，下面描述这两种方法。"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:94
msgid "1. Declaring a serializer in the field"
msgstr "1. 声明字段中的序列转换器"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:96
msgid ""
"If you use :class:`~scrapy.Item` you can declare a serializer in the :ref:"
"`field metadata <topics-items-fields>`. The serializer must be a callable "
"which receives a value and returns its serialized form."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:100 ../../../topics/exporters.rst:125
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "示例："

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:102
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"def serialize_price(value):\n"
"    return f\"$ {str(value)}\"\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class Product(scrapy.Item):\n"
"    name = scrapy.Field()\n"
"    price = scrapy.Field(serializer=serialize_price)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:117
msgid "2. Overriding the serialize_field() method"
msgstr "2. 覆盖 serialize_field() 方法"

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:119
msgid ""
"You can also override the :meth:`~BaseItemExporter.serialize_field` method "
"to customize how your field value will be exported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:122
msgid ""
"Make sure you call the base class :meth:`~BaseItemExporter.serialize_field` "
"method after your custom code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/exporters.rst:127
msgid ""
"from scrapy.exporters import XmlItemExporter\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class ProductXmlExporter(XmlItemExporter):\n"
"    def serialize_field(self, field, name, value):\n"
"        if name == \"price\":\n"
"            return f\"$ {str(value)}\"\n"
"        return super().serialize_field(field, name, value)"
msgstr ""
"来自废料。 xporters importer XmlItemExporter\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class ProductXmlExportter(XmlItemExporter):\n"
"    def serialize_field(自己, field, field, 名字，值：\n"
"        如果名称== \"价格\"：\n"
"            return f\"$ {str(value)}\"\n"
"        return super(). erialize_field(字段，名称，值)"

